## JavaScript Style

### Indentation & Spacing

```javascript
// Good: 2 spaces
function calculateTotal(items) {
  return items.reduce((sum, item) => {
    return sum + item.price
  }, 0)
}

// Bad: 4 spaces or tabs
function calculateTotal(items) {
    return items.reduce((sum, item) => {
        return sum + item.price
    }, 0)
}
```

### Variable Declarations

```javascript
// Good: const for constants
const MAX_ITEMS = 10
const API_URL = 'https://api.example.com'

// Good: let for variables that change
let totalCount = 0
let currentPage = 1

// Bad: var (use const/let instead)
var count = 0  // Don't use var
```

### Function Definitions

```javascript
// Good: Arrow functions for callbacks
items.map(item => item.name)
items.filter(item => item.active)

// Good: Traditional functions for methods
function calculateTotal(items) {
  return items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.price, 0)
}

// Good: Method shorthand in classes
class Calculator {
  calculateTotal(items) {
    return items.reduce((sum, item) => sum + item.price, 0)
  }
}
```

### String Templates

```javascript
// Good: Template literals for interpolation
const message = `Hello, ${userName}!`
const url = `/articles/${articleId}`

// Good: Single quotes for static strings
const status = 'active'
const category = 'technology'
```

### Object & Array Destructuring

```javascript
// Good: Use destructuring
const { name, email, age } = user
const [first, second, ...rest] = items

// Good: Destructuring in function parameters
function displayUser({ name, email }) {
  console.log(`${name}: ${email}`)
}
```

